# description = "This Griptape Nodes workflow is designed for Nuke integration to perform AI-driven image inpainting, utilizing **FLUX** diffusion models to seamlessly fill masked areas of an image based on user text prompts. The process begins by loading an RGB plate and an alpha mask, then uses a vision model to analyze the scene and automatically enhance the user's prompt into a highly detailed, context-aware description. Depending on a user-defined \"local\" toggle, the workflow automatically handles image resizing and routes the generation task through either a local diffusion pipeline (such as FLUX.1-Fill) or a remote proxy API (such as FLUX.2). Finally, the system rescales the newly generated image back to its original input resolution and saves the completed file to a specified output path."
